title: Jaws drop as CBA boss says the young don't think property prices are too high
text: | MP3 download The Chief Executive of the Commonwealth Bank says he doesn't believe young Australians regard house prices on the east coast as over-priced.The Commonwealth is the latest bank to front the Parliament's Economics Committee, as Australia's top bankers are grilled about everything from employee misconduct to credit card fees.But it was Ian Narev's comments about Sydney and Melbourne house prices that caused jaws to drop among some of the younger generation in the big cities.Featured: Sally Auld, chief economist, JP MorganJian Carlodestefano, student, University of Technology, Sydney
